            <p class="MsoNormal" align="center" style="text-align:center">
            <font color="#570E0A" size="2" face="Arial"><b><u>
            <span lang="EN-US">Welcome to&nbsp; Mendoza</span></u></b></font></p>
            <p class="MsoNormal" style="text-align:justify">
            <font color="#570E0A" size="2" face="Arial"><span lang="EN-US">
            Situated at the foot of The Andes, </span><b><span lang="EN-US">
            Mendoza</span></b><span lang="EN-US"> is the capital city of the 
            homonymous province and the most important city of the West of 
            Argentina. It is one of the most chosen tourist destinations because 
            of the various interesting activities available in the region. &nbsp;</span></font></p>
            <p class="MsoNormal" style="text-align:justify">
            <font color="#570E0A" size="2" face="Arial"><span lang="EN-US">The 
            city is well laid out and almost everything worth visiting is well 
            within walking distance.&nbsp;</span></font></p>
            <p class="MsoNormal" style="text-align:justify">
            <font color="#570E0A" size="2" face="Arial"><span lang="EN-US">You 
            come to Mendoza for the wineries, the excellent Argentinean food, 
            the Andes, the friendly people, the local shopping and for the 
            affordable pricing. <br>
            It is an incredible oasis to grow fruits and vegetables due to the 
            presence of the Mendoza and Tunuyán Rivers.</span></font></p>
            <p class="MsoNormal" style="text-align:justify">
            <font color="#570E0A" size="2" face="Arial"><span lang="EN-US">&nbsp;</span></font></p>
